723021f-a.title: Manhattan: Rockefeller Plaza - 49th Street (West)
723021f-a.text:
Rocketeller Plaza (center foreground), west side, from West 49th (left) to West 50th Streets (right), showing under construction the 70-story R.C.A. Building, within the Rockefeller Center development. The tall building on the right is the 31-story R.K.O. Building, facing on Sixth Ave., from West 50th to West 51st Streets, and preceding it is the International Music Hall, the largest and most magnificent motion picture theatre in the world. On the left is shown the Center Theatre, at the S.E. corner of West 49th Street. Also shown is a general view westward of the surrounding area with the Hudson River and the New Jersey
shore line visible in the background.
August 29, 1932.
Wurtr Brothers.

723031f-a.title: Manhattan: Rockefeller Plaza - 49th Street (West)
723031f-a.text:
Rockefeller Plaza, east side, between West 49th and 50th Streets. Shown at the northern half of this block front, is the completed British Empire Building. On the extreme right, appears La Maison Francaise (French
Building).
May 15, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

723034f-b.title: Manhattan: Rockefeller Plaza - 49th Street (West)
723034f-b.text:
Rockefeller Plara (left where men are standingJ, east side, between West 49th and West 50th Streets (within Enckefeller Center), showing the Prometheus Fountain and part of the open-air cafd at the western extremity of the Sunken Plana, which is approachable from Fifth Ave. through the Promenade. The statue created by one of America's greatest living sculptors, Paul Manship, shows the flying Prometheus with the life giving fire in his right hand. It is in gilded bronze and stands
in the midst of a Mranite basin.
August 24, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

723026f.title: Manhattan: Rockefeller Plaza - 49th Street (West)
723026f.text:
Rockefeller Plaza, west side, from W. 49th to 50th Street. This view shows the southerly exposure (W. 49th Street side) of the 70-storied R. C. A. Building. Rockefeller Plaza would be on
thr right and 6th Avenue on the left.
1938-9
Alexander Alland
Thisphoto is one of a series that appeared in the published volume "Portrait of N. Y." by Felix Reisenberg and Alex. Alland, IRGV.

723032f-b.title: Manhattan: Rockefeller Plaza - 49th Street (West)
723032f-b.text:
(1)
Rockefeller Plasa, between West 49th and 50th Streets, as seen from the Empire Trust Building (No. 580 Fifth Ave)., and showing the new Roxkefeller Center development. Steel structure is the future R.C.A. Building. Where the excavation is, the Plaza, Fountain, British and French
Buildings stand to-day (1937).
June 8, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
A view slightly eastward to Fifth Ave. Shown in the foregrond, is the Collegiate Church of St. Nicholas. Other prominent structure is the then new Goelet Building (608 Fifth Ave., at the S.W. corner of West
49th Street).
June 8, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same as No. 1, but at a later date. This view also shows
further demolition north of 50th to 51st Streets.
